"version": "1.0.4",
"title": "6185: imagination, inward desires",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6185",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The usually sinful inclinations of a heart which is by nature corrupt and stubborn, but which may be renewed by God, resulting in purified desires.</p>\n<h2>The heart is the source of human desires</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov4:23\">PRO 4:23</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps10:3\">PSA 10:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:34-Matt12:35\">MAT 12:34–12:35</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke6:45\">LUK 6:45</a></p>\n<h2>God knows the human heart</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs8:39\">1KI 8:39</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr28:9\">1CH 28:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam16:7\">1SA 16:7</a> <em>God's choice of David</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps7:9\">PSA 7:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:14\">PSA 19:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps26:2\">PSA 26:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps38:9\">PSA 38:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps44:21\">PSA 44:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:2\">PSA 139:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps139:23\">PSA 139:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov15:26\">PRO 15:26</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov21:2\">PRO 21:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:20\">JER 11:20</a> <em>The plot of Jeremiah's enemies is revealed to him by the LORD</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer20:12\">JER 20:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:5\">EZK 11:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev2:23\">REV 2:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt9:4\">MAT 9:4</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark2:8\">MRK 2:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke5:22\">LUK 5:22</a> <em>Jesus Christ knows the thoughts of others.</em></p>\n<h2>The corruption of the heart</h2>\n<h3>Its inclination towards evil</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen6:5\">GEN 6:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen8:21\">GEN 8:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps14:1-Ps14:3\">PSA 14:1–14:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps53:1-Ps53:3\">PSA 53:1–53:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps94:11\">PSA 94:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eccl9:3\">ECC 9:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer17:9-Jer17:10\">JER 17:9–17:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:18-Matt15:19\">MAT 15:18–15:19</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:20-Mark7:23\">MRK 7:20–7:23</a></p>\n<h3>Corruption finds particular expression in sexual sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:24\">ROM 1:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:28\">MAT 5:28</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:26-Rom1:27\">ROM 1:26–1:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:19\">GAL 5:19</a></p>\n<h2>The stubbornness of the heart</h2>\n<h3>It leads to disregard for God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa65:2\">ISA 65:2</a></strong></p>\n<h3>It produces false confidence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut29:18-Deut29:19\">DEU 29:18–29:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer23:17\">JER 23:17</a></p>\n<h3>It leads to idolatry</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer9:14\">JER 9:14</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer13:10\">JER 13:10</a></p>\n<h3>It leads to disobedience</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer7:24\">JER 7:24</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:12\">JER 16:12</a></p>\n<h3>It brings God's judgment</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer11:8\">JER 11:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov28:14\">PRO 28:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov29:1\">PRO 29:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer18:12-Jer18:13\">JER 18:12–18:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom2:5\">ROM 2:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb3:7-Heb3:11\">HEB 3:7–3:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps95:7-Ps95:11\">PSA 95:7–95:11</a></p>\n<h3>God allows people to continue in their stubbornness</h3>\n<p>God hardens Pharaoh's heart:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod4:21\">EXO 4:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod7:3\">EXO 7:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:4\">EXO 14:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod14:17\">EXO 14:17</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps81:11-Ps81:12\">PSA 81:11–81:12</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom1:28\">ROM 1:28</a></p>\n<h2>God's renewal of the heart</h2>\n<h3>It results in purified desires</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer24:7\">JER 24:7</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek36:26\">EZK 36:26</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut6:6\">DEU 6:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek11:19\">EZK 11:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:2\">ROM 12:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor4:6\">2CO 4:6</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:23\">EPH 4:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil4:8-Phil4:9\">PHP 4:8–4:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb8:10\">HEB 8:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer31:33\">JER 31:33</a></p>\n<h3>Examples of renewed hearts</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr11:16\">2CH 11:16</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh9:8\">NEH 9:8</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps51:10\">PSA 51:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps57:7\">PSA 57:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps86:11\">PSA 86:11</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer3:17\">JER 3:17</a></p>\n<h3>God delights in a pure heart</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps24:3-Ps24:5\">PSA 24:3–24:5</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut5:29\">DEU 5:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps73:1\">PSA 73:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps125:4\">PSA 125:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:8\">MAT 5:8</a></p>\n<h3>God fulfils the desires of hearts devoted to him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps37:4\">PSA 37:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps21:2\">PSA 21:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps145:19\">PSA 145:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:21\">MAT 6:21</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:34\">LUK 12:34</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt6:33\">MAT 6:33</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke12:31\">LUK 12:31</a></p>\n<h3>God gives the desire to follow him</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Chr29:18\">1CH 29:18</a></strong></p>\n<h2>The human ability to visualise in parables</h2>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:11-Matt13:17\">MAT 13:11–13:17</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:10-Matt4:12\">MAT 4:10–4:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:9-Luke8:10\">LUK 8:9–8:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke10:23-Luke10:24\">LUK 10:23–10:24</a></p>",
